      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level for model risk level 3.",
      "rationale": "Ansys Mechanical 2021 R2 is a commercially validated FEA solver with documented QA procedures, release notes, and regression test suites. FDA in-house scripts were verified against analytical benchmarks. Achieved level equals required level."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical code verification",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Code verification activities documented and traceable to published benchmarks.",
      "rationale": "Solver correctness verified against NAFEMS benchmark LE1 and patch-test solutions. Contact algorithm verified against Hertzian contact analytical solution. Results archived in project verification log VL-2021-003."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Discretization error",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Mesh convergence study demonstrating less than 5% change in QoI between successive refinements.",
      "rationale": "Three-level h-refinement study performed on pedicle screw shank and rod interface regions. Von Mises stress and construct stiffness QoIs changed by less than 2.1% between medium and fine meshes. Final mesh selected at medium refinement level for computational efficiency."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical solver error",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Residual convergence criteria met and documented for all load steps.",
      "rationale": "Newton-Raphson iterations converged to force residual below 1e-4 for all 11 model instances. No load-step bisections were required. Energy norm monitored and confirmed monotone decrease."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Use error",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Independent review of model setup, boundary conditions, and material assignments completed by a second analyst.",
      "rationale": "Model setup reviewed by a second FDA analyst not involved in primary model development. Boundary conditions, contact definitions, and material property assignments confirmed correct against F1717 test protocol. No discrepancies identified."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Model form assumptions documented and justified relative to the physics of F1717 compression-bending.",
      "rationale": "Linear elastic material model justified by pre-yield loading regime targeted in F1717 protocol. Frictional contact (mu=0.2) at screw-rod interface supported by literature values for titanium-on-titanium. Large-deformation formulation enabled to capture geometric nonlinearity at 5-degree loading angle."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Material properties and geometric inputs traceable to measured values with uncertainty characterization.",
      "rationale": "Titanium alloy (Ti-6Al-4V) elastic modulus and yield strength sourced from ASTM F136 material certificates for the specific lot used in physical testing. Geometry derived from CMM measurements of N=3 representative screws and rods. Dimensional uncertainty propagated via sensitivity analysis."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Test samples representative of production devices; sample size sufficient for statistical comparison.",
      "rationale": "N=11 constructs drawn from production lots with full material traceability. Sample size supports 90% confidence interval estimation on mean stiffness. Both laboratories used identical device lots to eliminate lot-to-lot variability as a confound."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Test conditions span the range of clinically relevant loading scenarios or deficiency is documented and accepted.",
      "rationale": "Testing performed at a single compression-bending load angle (5 degrees) per ASTM F1717. The required level of 3 is not achieved because no additional load angles or axial compressive pre-loads were evaluated. This deficiency is acknowledged; the single-condition limitation is accepted given the regulatory precedent for F1717 as a standard submission test."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Simulation inputs shown to be equivalent to experimental conditions within documented tolerances.",
      "rationale": "Applied displacement rate in simulation (quasi-static) confirmed equivalent to 5 mm/min crosshead speed used experimentally; inertial effects negligible. Fixture geometry in FEA reproduced from engineering drawings of test fixtures used at both laboratories. Grip compliance measured and incorporated as boundary condition spring elements."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Quantitative comparison metric defined a priori; FEA predictions within acceptance band for primary QoIs.",
      "rationale": "Primary QoIs are construct stiffness (N/mm) and yield load (N). A priori acceptance criterion: FEA prediction within 10% of experimental mean. FEA stiffness predictions fell within 6.3% of experimental mean across all 11 constructs; yield load predictions within 8.1%. Bland-Altman analysis confirmed no systematic bias."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "QoIs directly linked to the clinical and regulatory question of interest.",
      "rationale": "Construct stiffness and yield load are the primary mechanical endpoints specified in ASTM F1717 and referenced in FDA guidance for spinal fixation systems. These QoIs directly inform the regulatory decision on device mechanical performance adequacy."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Validation scenario sufficiently similar to intended use scenario to support credibility claim.",
      "rationale": "Validation activities replicate the ASTM F1717 test protocol that constitutes the regulatory use scenario. Device geometry, material, assembly torque, and loading mode in validation are identical to those in the intended submission test. The validation scenario is assessed as directly relevant to the COU for pre-market submission support."
    }
  ],
